Company Profile Extraction using LangChain & Cohere
ğŸ“Œ Overview

This project demonstrates how to build a structured information extraction pipeline using LangChain, Cohere LLM, and Pydantic.
The application takes a company name as input, fetches relevant data from Wikipedia, and extracts key company details in a validated, structured format.

The focus of this project is on:

Document loading

Prompt engineering

Output parsing and validation

Reliable LLM pipelines (not free-form text)

ğŸ¯ Features

ğŸ” Fetches company information directly from Wikipedia

ğŸ§  Uses Cohere LLM for intelligent data extraction

ğŸ§© Enforces a strict output schema using Pydantic

ğŸ“„ Produces consistent, structured company profiles

âš™ï¸ Built using modern LangChain runnable pipelines

