ğŸ“¦ Installation

Install all required dependencies:

pip install langchain langchain-community langchain-cohere pydantic wikipedia

ğŸ”‘ API Key Setup (Cohere)

Set your Cohere API key as an environment variable.

Option 1: Google Colab (Recommended)

Open Colab â†’ ğŸ”‘ Secrets

Add a secret:

Name: COHERE_API_KEY

Value: your Cohere API key

Then load it in code:

import os
from google.colab import userdata

os.environ["COHERE_API_KEY"] = userdata.get("COHERE_API_KEY")

Option 2: Local / Temporary Setup
import os
os.environ["COHERE_API_KEY"] = "YOUR_COHERE_API_KEY"

ğŸš€ How to Run the Project

Install dependencies

Configure the Cohere API key

Run the notebook cells in order

Enter a company name when prompted

Example input:

Google


Example output:

Company Name : Google
Founder      : Larry Page, Sergey Brin
Founded Date : 1998
Revenue      : USD 307 billion (2023)
Employees    : ~182,000

Summary:
1. Google is a multinational technology company.
2. It specializes in internet-related services and products.
3. The company operates under Alphabet Inc.
4. Google is a global leader in search and AI technologies.

ğŸ§  Key Learning Outcomes

This project demonstrates:

How to use document loaders for real-world data ingestion

How to design schema-driven LLM outputs

Why output parsers are essential for production systems

How to handle LLM unpredictability safely

How modern LangChain runnable pipelines work
